{"id": 239774866, "title": "Fintan Drury: We need a plan to tackle the insidious creep of racism here", "text": "The success of our athletes at the European Championships in Rome had resonances of Italia \u201990 and our exit in the eternal city\u2019s Olympic stadium to the host nation at the quarter-final stage of the World Cup. We\u2019d a team rich with talent but the most iconic and the best was Paul McGrath, a black Dubliner whose performances were critical to our success. Ireland loved him, unreservedly. Ireland has had some great individual athletes but, before last week, we had never been competitive in relays. Our track talent has been so limited that we never had \u2014 until now \u2014 four athletes good enough at the one time to be remotely competitive. Rome changed that; Irish athletes changed that; women and men wearing green vests produced extraordinary results, again showing the power sport has to generate positivity and lift a nation\u2019s spirits.", "summary": "<p>The success of our athletes at the European Championships in Rome had resonances of Italia \u201990 and our exit in the eternal city\u2019s Olympic stadium to the host nation at the quarter-final stage of the World Cup. We\u2019d a team rich with talent but the most iconic and the best was Paul McGrath, a black Dubliner whose performances were critical to our success. Ireland loved him, unreservedly. </p>", "url": "https://www.independent.ie/opinion/fintan-drury-we-need-a-plan-to-tackle-the-insidious-creep-of-racism-here/a1137924291.html", "image": "https://focus.independent.ie/thumbor/C-d_-EFAeEm6JWIWIoK1cqgBfCY=/0x0:960x640/550x550/prod-mh-ireland/86fec74e-03a6-4dc3-af40-f8a5f04e300d/dd86933b-48a8-420b-9db7-2e6b269fe757/86fec74e-03a6-4dc3-af40-f8a5f04e300d.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-23 01:30:00", "author": "Fintan Drury", "authors": ["Fintan Drury"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": 0.552}